  "prompt": "What is an example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users?",
  "response": "One notable example of a platform that leveraged another platform to gain users is Instagram. When Instagram launched in 2010, it allowed users to sign up and log in using their Facebook accounts. This integration provided Instagram with immediate access to Facebook's large user base, making it easier for new users to join without having to create a separate account. \n\nThe connection also encouraged users to share their Instagram photos directly on Facebook, further increasing visibility and encouraging friends and family to join the platform. This strategic leveraging of Facebook allowed Instagram to grow rapidly, ultimately leading to its acquisition by Facebook in 2012.",
